Part A: The Zero Line Foundation 

18
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:45,600
The Zero Line is your trend 
compass. Everything starts here. 

19
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:53,760
Here's what most traders see—MACD above zero, so 
they think "maybe bullish"…MACD below zero, so  

20
00:01:53,760 --> 00:02:00,800
they think "probably bearish" They're wishy-washy 
about it. They take sells above zero. They take  

21
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:09,120
buys below zero. They fight the trend constantly.
But here's what I do instead. Above zero equals I  

22
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:15,200
ONLY look for buys. Below zero equals 
I ONLY look for sells. No exceptions.  

23
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:20,240
The Zero Line is absolute law.
Watch this chart with me. Every  

24
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:26,880
time I ignored the Zero Line and bought below 
it, I lost money. See this buy signal below  

25
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:35,280
zero? Lost trade. This one? Another loser.
Now look at these buy signals above zero.  

26
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:43,040
