This is where it gets really interesting.

53
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:41,972
Now, the second system is the Reversal 
System. This catches the major turning points. 

54
00:05:41,972 --> 00:05:44,400
Part A: Divergence Detection
Let me show you a situation that happens  

55
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:51,600
literally every single day in every market.
Price makes a new high. Everyone's buying.  

56
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:56,240
The chart looks incredibly bullish. But 
there's a hidden warning signal that the  

57
00:05:56,240 --> 00:06:01,760
move is about to completely reverse.
The problem is price is lying to you.  

58
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:08,480
It's making new highs but it's running out of 
steam internally. Most traders can't see this  

59
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:15,360
exhaustion until it's way too late. They buy 
the top and then wonder why they always lose. 

60
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:22,000
What you want is to catch the reversal before 
it happens, not after you've already lost money. 

61
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:29,200
Here's how divergence works. When price makes 
a higher high but MACD makes a lower high,  

62
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:35,120
that's bearish divergence. The reversal is 
coming. Draw a line connecting the price  

63
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:42,320
tops. Draw another line connecting the MACD 
tops. When they disagree—when price goes up  

64
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:51,280
but MACD goes down—get ready for the reversal.
Watch this example. Price making new highs here,  

65
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:58,960
here, and here. But look at MACD. Lower 
high, lower high, lower high. The engine  

66
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:07,280
is dying while the car is still moving forward. 
2 days later….massive reversal. 200 point drop. 

67
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:13,840
The opposite works for bullish divergence. 
Price makes a lower low but MACD makes a  

68
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:22,480
higher low. That's a bottom forming. The selling 
is exhausted even though price is still falling. 

69
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:30,720
But wait—divergence alone isn't enough. I lost so 
much money entering on divergence alone. You need  

70
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:35,280
confirmation. That's where the histogram comes in.
Part B: Histogram Confirmation 

71
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:42,560
The histogram is your momentum reader. These 
bars tell you exactly when momentum is shifting. 

72
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:46,240
Let me show you the three 
patterns that actually matter. 

73
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:54,240
First pattern—The Flip. See this first green bar 
after five red bars? That's momentum shifting from  

74
00:07:54,240 --> 00:08:01,680
bearish to bullish. You might think it's just one 
random bar. But watch what happens next. Complete  

75
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:08,880
reversal. The histogram saw it coming.
Second pattern—The Shrinking Tower.  

76
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:14,800
Look at these bars getting smaller and 
smaller. Red bars shrinking? Selling  

77
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:23,280
is dying. Green bars shrinking? Buying is 
exhausted. The move is running out of gas. 

78
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:30,640
Third pattern—The Zero Bounce. Watch the 
histogram approach the zero line then bounce away.  

79
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:37,200
The trend just proved it still has 
power. It's continuing, not reversing. 

80
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:44,000
Here's how you combine them. You spot divergence 
first—that's your alert. Then you wait for a  

81
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:52,160
histogram pattern—that's your trigger. Divergence 
plus histogram pattern equals reversal trade. 

82
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:59,200
Look at this trade. Bearish divergence on the 
4-hour chart. Histogram showing shrinking green  

83
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:07,600
bars. Then boom—first red bar. That was my 
entry signal. Caught a 100 pip reversal. 

84
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:12,960
These two MACD strategies will bring 
you a lot of good trades. But Strategy  

85
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:18,880
